<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: duhub</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-28 16:28:10</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This must have been a mistake by the programmers. Either it was named wrong, or set to go in the wrong slot.  For those of you posting that it isn't such a great item, I'd like to point out the typical Wisdom to Mana conversion:<BR>
<BR>
I am a 34th level cleric.  Using a mana calculator found at http://eq.castersrealm.com I found out that currently at my level, 1 point of Wisdom is equal to 6 points of actual mana.  That means that for me a +25 Mana item acts like a little over 4 additional Wisdom.  Since this item already has +5 Wisdom, with the +25 Mana it's almost like having a +9 Wisdom item (or a +55 Mana item).  In my opinion, thats VERY impressive.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
